  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The resilience and security of land and environmental defenders are strengthened through the protection and moral support provided through international accompaniment and observation.</narrative>
  </description>
  <participating-org ref="US-EIN-US-EIN-91-1179750" role="4" type="21">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Peace Brigades International</narrative>
  </participating-org>
  <activity-status code="2"></activity-status>
  <activity-date iso-date="2020-01-01" type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Since the beginning of the project, PBI has developed different strategies to support defenders of land, territory and the environment in Honduras, Guatemala and Nicaragua, through activities such as accompaniments, observations, visits to offices and bilateral meetings. with the accompanied organizations to learn about their needs in terms of protection, risk situation and exchange information. Specifically, 276 human rights defenders have received ongoing or occasional support from PBI in these two years (conditions arising from the COVID-19 pandemic, which have particularly affected Central American countries in the last quarter of 2020 and the first half of 2020). 2021, have limited the number of activities with new participants, although work with the beneficiaries of the first year is maintained).</narrative>
